"43:8:2" : {s: 43, a: 8, w: 2, r: "شدد", t: "أَشَدَّ", l: "أَشَدّ", lc: 31, tl: "ashadda", lb: "কঠোর, অধিক শক্ত",e: "stronger", b: "(যারা ছিল) প্রবলতর", i: "sangat", f: 9, rm: "to bind tightly, strap, strengthen firmly, run, establish, make firm, hard, strong, be advanced (day), be intense. ushdud - harden, strengthen. shadiid (pl. shidaad & ashiddau - great, firm, strict, vehement, strong, violent, severe, mighty, terrible, stern, grievous, miserly, niggardly. (adj. of the forms faiil and fiaal are used indifferently for both m. and f.): ashuddun: age of full strength, maturity. ishtadda (vb. 8) - to act with violence, become hard.", ag: "أسم منصوب", eg: "Noun Accusative case", tag: "N", pos: "N", att: "ACC", qual: "", deg: "", gen: "M", num: "S", mood: "", lu: "أَشَدُّ،شَدِيدٌۭ،شَدِيدُ،ٱشْدُدْ"},
